KAIZER Chiefs confirms the appointment of former player and captain Patrick Mabedi as the new Assistant Coach.&nbsp;Mabedi penned a two year deal from July 1, 2017. &nbsp;He is replacing John Paintsil whose contract was terminated with immediate effect last Thursday (8 June).The Malawian born played for Amakhosi from 1998 to 2006. The 43 year old Mabedi enjoyed a glorious career as a Glamour Boy winning numerous trophies including the back to back Premiership titles in 2003/4 and 2004/5 plus the Mandela Cup in 2001.Mabedi also captained the team from 2003-2006 before leaving Chiefs to complete his career with Moroka Swallows.He said: &ldquo;I am happy to be back home, this is a privilege. I look forward to making a contribution to the success of this great institution. &nbsp;I wish to thank the Club Management for this opportunity.&rdquo;Mabedi joins Chiefs from Cape Town All Stars where he was head coach.&nbsp;Mabedi is the new Chiefs assistant coach https://t.co/ErB4uMG5PT #WelcomeBackMabedi #Amakhosi4Life&mdash; Kaizer Chiefs (@KaizerChiefs) June 13, 2017